Spain ' s BBV to buy back 45 pct in Finanzia by GE . Spanish bank Banco Bilbao Vizcaya ( BBV ) said on Friday it would buy back from General Electric Capital Services 45 percent of the bank Finanzia . In a statement , BBV added it would then have 100 percent of this bank , which operates in consumer financing . In addition , BBV will sell to General Electric Capital corporation its 20 percent holding in General Electric Capital Corporation of Puerto Rico . Earlier on Friday BBV had also said it would buy back the 1 . 8 percent BBV stake from General Electric Capital . BBV said in a statement the deals have been reached with friendly relationships , and they are not ruling out further agreements . - - Madrid Newsroom , + 341 585 8340 
